<title>ITALY: MIB30-Compart replaces Mediolanum.</title>
<headline>MIB30-Compart replaces Mediolanum.</headline>
<dateline>MILAN 1997-03-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Italian financial holding Compart, formerly Ferruzzi Finanziaria, will replace insurance and financial services group Mediolanum in the Milan Bourse Mib30 index of blue chip stocks from March 24, the Bourse Council said in a statement.</p>
<p>Compart left the blue chip index in September, the last time it was revised, and Mediolanum entered.  </p>
<p>The basket of 30 stocks is revised twice a year.</p>
<p>The Bourse Council said the weightings with which the individual shares will enter the basket will be fixed on the morning of March 24 using opening prices and values relative to the number of shares in circulation.</p>
<p>-- Milan newsroom +392 66129589</p>
